  				<h2 class="noTopMargin">Visual Designer</h2>
	        	<p>Location: Pune, India</p>
	        	<p>
	        	    We are looking for a talented digital designer with 1-5 years of experience designing for web browsers.
	        	</p>    
            <h4>Job Responsibilities</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Translate market and product requirements into conceptual interaction models (wireframes, mockups, interactive prototypes) and use them to communicate the user experience requirements to clients and team members</li>
                <li>Work closely with clients, technical team leads, and engineers to oversee the user experience of a product from beginning to end</li>
                <li>Design assets for client brands, web sites, and web/mobile products including logos, emails, infographics, and data charts</li>
                <li>Ensure consistency of vision/design with overall site or brand for each client</li>
                <li>Set typographic standards and oversee that type and production details have been applied and are consistent throughout a publication or site</li>
            </ul>
	        	    
            <h4>Requirements</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>1+ years work experience in the design field</li>
                <li>Demonstrated understanding of and appreciation for a user's experience of a site or product</li>
                <li>Experience with common web and mobile UX elements such as pop-ups/modals, sliders, drop-down trays, mouseovers, etc.  Ability to discuss pros and cons of such elements in various situations</li>
                <li>Familiarity with basic and common application user flows such as login, registration, account management, and e-mail notifications</li>
                <li>Proficiency with relevant design software, including Illustrator and Photoshop for Macs as well as basic knowledge of the printing process</li>
                <li>Good organizational abilities and detail-orientation with the ability to multi-task, including working on multiple projects and successfully meeting deadlines</li>
                <li>A team player with strong interpersonal skills; a positive, collegial attitude; a high level of professionalism, and the ability to work collaboratively in a close team structure</li>
                <li>A willingness to accept constructive criticism and direction, while also being able to articulate decisions made and defend you work</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h4>Education</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>A Bachelors degree or equivalent and formal education in graphic design</li>
              <li>Artistic sensibility and a portfolio showcasing design and typographic skills</li>
            </ul>
            
